Four abandoned puppies found shivering in the rain and doused with gasoline at a mobile home park in Arizona are being put up for adoption.

The German shepherd mixes were found in a grey plastic box by a resident of the mobile park in West Phoenix on Friday.

Joey Friend, who rescued the dogs, said the sight of the trembling puppies doused in fuel ‘was horrible’.

