‘They had sores from the diesel fuel [because of their] tender skin,’ he told AZFamily.com.

The puppies were rushed to Maricopa County Animal Care & Control for treatment.

‘They were cold and shivery and just covered in gas,’ MCACC spokeswoman Mellissa Gable said.

It took several baths and many hours to clean the two-month-old pups - three females and one male – according to Gable.

